@Node main

  ReqPatcher v0.0 [preview] - BlaBla product

  The guide seems to be small but.. what should I write about the stuff I wrote? The program is VERY easy to use...

  @{" What's that???  " Link a} - A short description
  @{" What do I need? " Link b} - Required configuration
  @{" Configuration   " Link c} - How to configure?
  @{" Developers      " Link d} - Programmers only :)
  @{" Author          " Link e} - me ;)
@endnode

@node a "What is it?"

  Well, ReqPatcher is a @{b}patch@{ub} which improves the look of system requesters a bit. The included file is only a @{b}preview@{ub} of the real stuff [being currently "under construction" ;)]

  I take no responsibility blah blah blah... You know the rest ;)
@endnode

@node b "Requirements"

Ahemm.. the most important part this patcher won't work without is..

- an Amiga - please, do be so kind and DON'T use it on UAE.
- OS - at least v3.0
- datatypes.library - any version
- locale.library - any version
- asl.library - any version

Of course, the better configuration You have, the better it works :)
@endnode

@node c "How to configure?"

@{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Global @{bg back}@{fg text}
  @{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Patches @{bg back}@{fg text}

  @{b}EasyRequestArgs@{ub}
    checked = patch the EasyRequestArgs() function

  @{b}BuildEasyRequest@{ub}
    checked = patch the BuildEasyRequestArgs() function

  @{b}BuildSysRequest@{ub}
    disabled [not yet supported]

  @{b}ReqToolsRequest@{ub}
    disabled [not yet supported]


@{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Options @{bg back}@{fg text}

  @{b}BG pictures@{ub}
    checked = use background patterns

  @{b}Disable requesters@{ub}
    checked = parse the requesters from @{b}Requesters@{ub} page

  @{b}Assign wedge@{ub}
    checked = parse a specific DOS request

  @{b}[EMPTY]@{ub}
    disabled [got no idea what to put here]


@{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Patterns @{bg back}@{fg text}

  [I suppose that the list doesn't need to be introduced hehe ;)]

  @{b}Req FG@{ub}
    checked - desired pattern will be used as the requester's body background

  @{b}Req BG@{ub}
    checked - desired pattern will be used as the requester's window background

  @{b}But FG@{ub}
    checked - desired pattern will be used as the requester's gadgets bg [normal state]

  @{b}But BG@{ub}
    checked - desired pattern will be used as the requester's gadgets bg [pressed state]


@{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Requesters @{bg back}@{fg text}

  [Just like above, the list won't be introduced]

  @{b}Title@{ub}
    requester's title

  @{b}Body@{ub}
    requester's body text

  @{b}Gads@{ub}
    requester's gadgets (separated by "|")

  @{b}Delay@{ub}
    minimal display time in seconds [0 = don't popup requester]

  @{b}GadgetID@{ub}
    the return value that will be returned after the time is over

@{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Advanced @{bg back}@{fg text}
  @{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Message @{bg back}@{fg text}

  @{b}Left@{ub}
    define the offset between the message field and left window border

  @{b}Top@{ub}
    Same for the top border

  @{b}Right@{ub}
    Once again - the right one...

  @{b}Bottom@{ub}
    ...and the bottom one.

  @{b}Spacing@{ub}
    Define the distance between each line

  @{b}Font@{ub}
    font to be used to write the message


  @{fg shine}@{bg shadow} Buttons @{bg back}@{fg text}

  @{b}Width (%)@{ub}
    minimal width of each button, that is, the largest button text's length * xx%.

  @{b}Height (%)@{ub}
    the button's height, that is, the font's Y size * xx%

  @{b}Spacing@{ub}
    Distance between each gadget

  @{b}Font@{ub}
    font to be used to write the texts inside the buttons.


@endnode
@node d "Developers"

    It seems to be some kind-of-abnormal to define more stuff in a patcher, but who knows, maybe someone will find it useful one day :). When declaring the body text You may use some escape codes [currently only three :)] - esc r, esc c and esc l [justification: right, centre and left]. Some additional tags may be specified in the new field of easystruct, but this is currently for internal use only.
@endnode

